# previousSibling

**Instance Property**

Returns the previous `NSXMLNode` object that is a sibling node to the receiver.

## Declaration

```swift
@NSCopying var previousSibling: XMLNode? { get }
```

## Discussion

This object will have an [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/XMLNode/index] value that is one less than the receiver’s. If there are no more previous siblings (that is, other child nodes of the receiver’s parent) the method returns `nil`

## Navigating the Tree of Nodes

- **rootDocument**: Returns the [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/XMLDocument] object containing the root element and representing the XML document as a whole.
- **parent**: Returns the parent node of the receiver.
- **child(at:)**: Returns the child node of the receiver at the specified location.
- **childCount**: Returns the number of child nodes the receiver has.
- **children**: Returns an immutable array containing the child nodes of the receiver (as `NSXMLNode` objects).
- **next**: Returns the next `NSXMLNode` object in document order.
- **nextSibling**: Returns the next `NSXMLNode` object that is a sibling node to the receiver.
- **previous**: Returns the previous `NSXMLNode` object in document order.
- **detach()**: Detaches the receiver from its parent node.
